bio:
I've now been 3D printing for a couple of years. I built my first printer as part of a part work subscription, (the Vector V3). It works well, but has it's limitations, the main one being its print bed size. So, I invested in the FLSUN i3 (2017). It has a print bed of 8" x 8" x 8", more than double the volume of the V3. This obviously allows me to print bigger models, with less cutting. I now have a Peopoly Moai SLA printer. I bought it as a kit. I did this as I find I learn more about the printer itself while building it, than I would buying a 'ready made' one. I'll be using my FDM printers for large, less detailed parts. The Moai will be used to produce any smaller, finer detailed parts.

My hobbies include golf, photography & the history of my home town, which is Lincoln.

bio:
Trideus is the major distributor for desktop 3D-Printing systems in the BENELUX countries. (Belgium, The Netherlands and Luxembourg).

Limit 3D-printing to the big companies? Off course not, not anymore! We at Trideus try to uncover 3D-printing to everybody. We give hobbyist, designers and fans of gadgets the opportunity to browse a big range of high qualitative, affordable 3D-printers, resources and accessories of different manufacturers. Customers that want to discover 3D printing, or who want a personal demonstration before purchasing, can visit our showroom in Ham.

Our ambitions? Excessive. Like is suited for a young, dynamic and energetic company! We strive on becoming the expert in 3D-printing for individuals and semi-professionals. Our business philosophy relies on these important pillars:

We give independent advice on our offer of 3D-printers, resources and accessories.
We want to make 3D-printing accessible and affordable for everybody, from hobbyist to semi-professional user.
We support our online offer with focused advice and demonstrations in our showroom.
To sum up: our 3D-printstory always starts from your expectations and specific needs. The unique combination of a webshop, a showroom and elaborate advice is your guarantee on quality and excellent service. Before, during and after your purchase.

I've been an avid 3D enthusiast for as long as I can remember, been designing in 3D since the mid-80's. 3D printing seemed a natural fit, so I purchased a Thing-O-Matic kit in November 2011. Sixteen hours after I cut the packing tape I attempted my first print and it was nearly perfect! I have great admiration for the early MakerBot designs, they were 'elegant' for lack of a better term. As of May 2016 I purchased and built a SeeMeCNC RoStock Max v2. It's a delta printer and it's fast! It took a little longer to put together but it has a massive build area, couldn't be happier!

I use Cinema 4D for my design application, it has just the right mix of tools for what I need. I use a Kinect/Skanect combo to digitize rough models, I'm still looking at other 3D scanners but haven't found one I want to invest in or build at the moment. I have a degree in electrical design so I use 3D printing for a lot of small electronic projects. My daughter 'commissions' me to create items for her cosplay costumes, one of our best collaborations has been a RotJ Thermal Detonator.

I love challenges so if you have a tough item to model leave me a comment, you just may be surprised with a response. Hope you enjoy my designs, leave comments if possible, I'd like to know what you think!

I first was introduced with 3D printing back in 2012. I was closely involved with Fablab Maastricht in the Netherlands. Back then 3D printing didn' t have the possibilities it has nowadays. A 3D printer was a highly technical device and it took many many hours to put a kit together. I lost contact with the fablab but end of 2016 I decided I wanted to pick it up again. I ordered a Chinese 3D printer DIY kit and after a long wait for delivery, I put it together. Since it was not that good quality, I learned a LOT about tinkering and getting everything to work. With quite a few upgrades the Chinese printer gives great results. Next step will be a Core-XY type printer with a larger build volume, so customers can also order larger objects.
My aim is to be able to give premium support and quick delivery on any orders.

bio:
Started off printing with a Makerbot Mini, great for plugging in and pressing print from thingiverse app. Very easy to get started on. I just got a Maker Select Plus from Monoprice and while it might or might not be an "upgrade" in considering it an upgrade because I can make this printer be what I want. Already added the larger fan and printed the 3D 360 degree fan shroud, added a glass bed, and octoprint with a USB camera. might add the auto leveling feature, x axis brace and who know what after all that.

I'm also into ham radio, I'm a Net Control Station for my local club www.marc-radio.org on some Wednesday nights. i also use APRS, and use the radios with a computer for digital modes like FT8. So that's all for now.
73 de KC3IGM

Hello, I am a former Hollywood set Designer and Prop maker for Movie, TV, Event, Stage and Video productions. Also Illustrator lighting specialist and Commercial Property Designer. I guess you could say I am Designer ADD. Now I get to play in my studio full time and enjoy a less stressful life due to heart conditions that limit my endurance. I still can't really shut it off, so I teach classes and make miniature scenes and replicas of about anything you can imagine. I love to wire about anything for lights in about any voltage. My grandfather was a master electrician and taught me how to wire a doll house when I was 5. well, he created a wiring maniac. love to work with micro motors and animate miniature scenes as well. thanks for taking the time to view my info. hav Phun!
